eu.stratosphere.nephele.io

Interface OutputGate<T extends Record>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of record that can be transported through this gate
    All Superinterfaces:
    Gate<T>

    public interface OutputGate<T extends Record>
extends Gate<T>
    In Nephele output gates are a specialization of general gates and connect record writers and output channels. As channels, output gates are always parameterized to a specific type of record which they can transport.
    Author:
    warneke

    • Method Detail

      • writeRecord

        void writeRecord(T record)
          throws java.io.IOException,
                 java.lang.InterruptedException
        Writes a record to one of the associated output channels. Currently, the channels are chosen in a simple round-robin fashion. This operation may block until the respective channel has received the data.
        Parameters:
        record - the record to be written
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - thrown if any error occurs during channel I/O
        java.lang.InterruptedException

      • flush

        void flush()
    throws java.io.IOException,
           java.lang.InterruptedException
        Flushes all connected output channels.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - thrown if an error occurs while flushing an output channel
        java.lang.InterruptedException - thrown if the thread is interrupted while waiting for the data to be flushed

      • isBroadcast

        boolean isBroadcast()
        Checks if this output gate operates in broadcast mode, i.e. all records passed to it are transferred through all connected output channels.
        Returns:
        true if this output gate operates in broadcast mode, false otherwise

      • getChannelSelector

        ChannelSelector<T> getChannelSelector()

      • requestClose

        void requestClose()
           throws java.io.IOException,

        Requests the output gate to closed. This means the application will send no records through this gate anymore.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
